    <p>The process for installing the memphis or sacramento deployment requires several JSON files
            that will be used when deploying the lifecycle manager.</p>
        
<section id="sample-node-provisionjson-file">
            <p>The following represents a sample <codeph>ldap.json</codeph> file in the
                    <codeph>/var/hlm/clouds/&lt;cloudname&gt;/vars</codeph> directory of the
                lifecycle manager. The IP addresses are masked for security purposes. Use values
                appropriate for your environment.</p>
            <p>The user admin name and password must be present in LDAP:</p>
            <p>
                <codeblock>"ldap_username": "admin", 
"ldap_password": "admin_001", </codeblock>
            </p>
            <codeblock>{
    "product": {
        "version": 1
    },

    "property-groups": [
        {
            "name": "ldap-vars",
            "properties": {
                "ldap_domain_name": "americas",
                "ldap_url": "10.x.x.x",
                "ldap_username": "admin",
                "ldap_password": "admin",
                "ldap_domain": "dc=helioncg,dc=local",
                "ldap_ou": "CGTestUsers",
                "ldap_nova_password": "nova",
                "ldap_nova_user": "nova",
                "ldap_neutron_password": "neutron",
                "ldap_neutron_user": "neutron",
                "ldap_cinder_password": "cinder",
                "ldap_cinder_user": "cinder",
                "ldap_glance_password": "glance",
                "ldap_glance_user": "glance",
                "ldap_enabled": 1
            }
        }
    ]
}</codeblock>
        </section>
